Setting up a payment system in TikTok depends on what you want to do—because TikTok has two completely different payment sides:

💸 You PAY TikTok (for ads)
💰 TikTok pays YOU (creator earnings / monetization)

For CPA marketing, you mostly need #1 (Ads payment setup) 👇

💳 1. Set Payment Method for TikTok Ads (IMPORTANT)

To run ads, use:
👉 TikTok Ads Manager

✅ Steps:
🔹 Step 1: Create Ads Account
Go to TikTok Ads Manager
Sign up with your TikTok account
🔹 Step 2: Go to Billing Settings

Inside Ads Manager:
👉 Dashboard → Tools → Billing

🔹 Step 3: Add Payment Method

TikTok supports:

💳 Visa / MasterCard
🏦 Bank Transfer (limited countries)
💰 Prepaid balance

👉 In Bangladesh, best option:
✔ International Debit/Credit Card

🔹 Step 4: Choose Payment Type
🔸 Auto Payment (Recommended)
Ads run first
TikTok charges you later
🔸 Manual Payment
Add balance first
Ads run until balance ends

👉 Beginners → Use Manual Payment (safe control)

💰 2. TikTok Paying YOU (Optional)

If you want to earn from TikTok directly:

Requirements:
10K+ followers
100K video views (last 30 days)

Then join:

Creator Fund
Live Gifts
TikTok Creativity Program

👉 But for CPA marketing:
❌ Not required

🔗 3. Payment Flow for CPA (Important Understanding)

Your setup will be:

👉 TikTok Ads (you pay)
→ Landing Page
→ CPA Offer
→ CPA Network pays YOU

Example:

You spend $20 on ads
You earn $100 from CPA
👉 Profit = $80
⚠️ Common Mistakes

❌ Trying to add Payoneer in TikTok Ads (not supported)
❌ Running ads without payment setup
❌ Using invalid cards → account suspension

🔥 Pro Tips (For You)

Since you're doing CPA:

✔ Start with small budget ($5–$10/day)
✔ Test multiple ads
✔ Track conversion (very important)
✔ Use landing page (not direct CPA link)

🧠 Simple Summary
TikTok Ads = You add card & pay
CPA Network = They pay you
No direct connection between TikTok & CPA payments



